This paper deals with distributed optimization in the presence of Byzantine adversaries, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning and optimization. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves encoding and error correction, which are topics related to information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also deals with security and cryptography, which could place it under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper involves coordination and communication between multiple nodes, which could place it under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
